[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: GHOST Document Retrieval and Reranking Requirements
UID: GHOST-DOCUMENT-RETRIEVAL-RERANKING
VERSION: 0.1
OPTIONS:
  MARKUP: Text
  AUTO_LEVELS: On
  NODE_IN_TOC: True

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 1. Purpose and Scope

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This document defines query-time document retrieval and optional reranking within GHOST Knowledge Management.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-ROOT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Document Retrieval and Reranking Scope
STATEMENT: >>>
GHOST shall retrieve query-relevant document chunks from an active project, optionally apply SPLADE and ColBERT ranking branches, hydrate selected chunks from raw sources, and write ordered candidate state into SuperPrompt for A3 evidence selection.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-SRS-FILE-TREE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-PRODUCT-NAME
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Product and Package Naming Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
The product described by this document shall be named GHOST; current Python paths may remain under ragstream.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-KM-PARENT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Retrieval Knowledge Management Parent
STATEMENT: >>>
Document Retrieval and Reranking shall be governed by the capability boundaries, shared artifacts, configuration governance, and sibling ownership defined in 40_knowledge_management.sdoc.

This document shall refine the retrieval/reranking sub-capability without redefining ingestion, A3, A4, or Memory Management.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-BOUNDARY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Retrieval Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
This document shall own query projection consumption, query splitting, dense ranking, SPLADE rescoring, reciprocal-rank fusion, hydration, retrieval-stage write-back, optional ColBERT reranking, and reranked-stage write-back.

It shall not own ingestion, A3 usefulness decisions, A4 condensation, memory retrieval, or final prompt composition.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-COMPONENTS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Retrieval Components
STATEMENT: >>>
The current capability shall be organized around Retriever, RetrieverEmb, RetrieverSplade, rrf_merge, smart_query_splitter, Chunk hydration, and Reranker.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-ROOT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 2. Retrieval Input and Query Projection

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Retrieval consumes the prepared SuperPrompt rather than reparsing raw input.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SP
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: SuperPrompt Input
STATEMENT: >>>
Retriever shall receive the active prepared SuperPrompt, active project name, requested top_k, and SPLADE enable/bypass choice.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-QUERY-PROJECTOR
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Query Projection Source
STATEMENT: >>>
Retriever shall obtain document query text through SuperPromptProjector.build_query_text.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SP

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-ROUTING
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: ActiveBrief Routing Compliance
STATEMENT: >>>
The query text used for retrieval shall reflect the finalized prompt-materiality/topic-relation policy established by PreProcessing.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-QUERY-PROJECTOR

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-EMPTY-SUPPRESSION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Empty Query Suppression
STATEMENT: >>>
A deliberately empty document query produced by the routing policy shall suppress document retrieval and shall not be replaced by prompt_ready, memory context, or an unrelated fallback.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-ROUTING

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-PROJECT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Project Name
STATEMENT: >>>
The project name shall be non-empty and shall identify one project-specific dense store and raw-document subtree.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SP

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-TOPK
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Requested Candidate Limit
STATEMENT: >>>
The requested top_k shall define the maximum fused retrieval rows returned by the retrieval stage when positive.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SP

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-NO-MEMORY-QUERY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Memory Query Ownership
STATEMENT: >>>
Document Retriever shall not query the memory vector store or MemoryIndexLookup.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SP

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 3. Deterministic Query Splitting

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The current smart_query_splitter is a deterministic linear overlapping splitter, not yet a semantic splitter.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-QUERY-SPLIT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Query Piece Generation
STATEMENT: >>>
The projected query shall be split into ordered overlapping text pieces before dense and sparse scoring.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-QUERY-TRIM
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Query Trim
STATEMENT: >>>
Query splitting shall trim the complete query and shall return an empty list when no usable text remains.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-QUERY-SPLIT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-QUERY-CHUNKER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Shared Chunker Use
STATEMENT: >>>
The current query splitter shall reuse the deterministic Chunker windowing algorithm.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-QUERY-SPLIT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-QUERY-SIZE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Query Window Validation
STATEMENT: >>>
Query chunk size shall be positive; overlap shall be non-negative and smaller than chunk size.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-QUERY-SPLIT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-QUERY-BASELINE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Query Window Baseline
STATEMENT: >>>
The current query-splitting baseline shall use 1200-character windows with 120-character overlap until replaced by approved runtime configuration.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-QUERY-SPLIT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-QUERY-ORDER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Query Piece Order
STATEMENT: >>>
Returned query pieces shall preserve the order produced by deterministic windowing and shall exclude empty pieces.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-QUERY-SPLIT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-NO-SMART-CLAIM
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Semantic Splitter Claim
STATEMENT: >>>
The current smart_query_splitter module shall not be described as semantic, sentence-aware, or LLM-based while its implementation remains linear character windowing.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-QUERY-SPLIT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 4. Dense Candidate Generation

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Dense retrieval is the mandatory first candidate-generation branch.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-DENSE-FIRST
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Dense First-Pass Retrieval
STATEMENT: >>>
RetrieverEmb shall generate the initial candidate set from the active project Chroma document store.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-DENSE-NEUTRAL
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Dense Backend State Neutrality
STATEMENT: >>>
RetrieverEmb shall receive project name, query pieces, and top_k without knowledge of SuperPrompt write-back or raw-file hydration.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-DENSE-FIRST

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-DENSE-STORE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Dense Store Validation
STATEMENT: >>>
Dense retrieval shall fail explicitly when the Chroma root or active project store does not exist.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-DENSE-FIRST

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-DENSE-EMPTY-QUERY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Dense Empty Query
STATEMENT: >>>
Dense retrieval shall return no rows when query pieces are empty.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-DENSE-FIRST

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-DENSE-READ
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Dense Store Read Contract
STATEMENT: >>>
Dense retrieval shall read stored chunk identifiers, embeddings, and metadata from the active project collection.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-DENSE-FIRST

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-DENSE-LENGTH
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Dense Store Shape Validation
STATEMENT: >>>
Dense retrieval shall reject mismatched identifier/embedding lengths and mismatched non-empty metadata lengths.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-DENSE-FIRST

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-DENSE-QUERY-EMBED
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Query Embedding
STATEMENT: >>>
The dense backend shall embed all query pieces using the configured dense Embedder.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-DENSE-FIRST

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-DENSE-DIM
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Embedding Dimension Validation
STATEMENT: >>>
Stored and query embedding matrices shall be two-dimensional and shall have equal vector dimensions.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-DENSE-FIRST

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-COSINE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Cosine Similarity
STATEMENT: >>>
The dense backend shall row-normalize stored and query vectors and shall compute cosine similarities by matrix multiplication.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-DENSE-FIRST

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-PNORM
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Query-Piece Aggregation
STATEMENT: >>>
Per-chunk dense similarities across query pieces shall be clipped at zero and aggregated by p-norm mean.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-DENSE-FIRST

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-PNORM-P
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Dense p Value
STATEMENT: >>>
The current dense p-norm aggregation baseline shall use p = 10 until replaced by approved configuration.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-PNORM

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-DENSE-SORT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Dense Deterministic Sort
STATEMENT: >>>
Dense rows shall be ordered by descending aggregated score and then ascending chunk identifier for ties.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-DENSE-FIRST

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-DENSE-CUTOFF
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Dense Candidate Cutoff
STATEMENT: >>>
Dense retrieval shall return no more than the positive requested top_k or its documented fallback when the caller supplies no valid positive limit.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-DENSE-FIRST

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 5. Hard Embedding Floor

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The dense result is filtered before SPLADE scoring and first fusion.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-EMB-FLOOR
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Hard Dense Similarity Floor
STATEMENT: >>>
Retriever shall remove dense candidate rows whose dense score is below the configured hard_embedding_floor.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-DENSE-FIRST

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-EMB-FLOOR-ZERO
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Disabled Floor
STATEMENT: >>>
A non-positive hard_embedding_floor shall disable dense-floor filtering.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-EMB-FLOOR

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-EMB-FLOOR-SOURCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Floor Configuration Source
STATEMENT: >>>
The current hard embedding floor shall be read from runtime_config.document_retrieval.hard_embedding_floor.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-EMB-FLOOR

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-EMB-FLOOR-META
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Floor Score Meaning
STATEMENT: >>>
The score compared to hard_embedding_floor shall be the aggregated dense embedding score later projected as emb_score.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-EMB-FLOOR

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 6. Optional SPLADE Rescoring Branch

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The current SPLADE branch rescoring scope is bounded by dense-selected candidate identifiers.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-OPTION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: SPLADE Enable Switch
STATEMENT: >>>
Retriever shall accept an explicit use_retrieval_splade switch.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-LAZY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Lazy Sparse Initialization
STATEMENT: >>>
The SPLADE encoder and RetrieverSplade backend shall be initialized lazily on first enabled use.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-OPTION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-CANDIDATES
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Dense-Bounded Sparse Candidates
STATEMENT: >>>
When enabled, RetrieverSplade shall score exactly the unique ordered identifiers surviving dense retrieval and hard-floor filtering.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-OPTION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-NOT-INDEPENDENT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Independent Sparse Search Claim
STATEMENT: >>>
The current enabled SPLADE branch shall not be described as an independent global sparse candidate generator because it receives dense-selected candidate_ids.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-CANDIDATES

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-STORE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Sparse Store Validation
STATEMENT: >>>
Enabled sparse retrieval shall validate the SPLADE root and active project store.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-OPTION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-MISSING-ID
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Sparse Candidate Alignment
STATEMENT: >>>
Every dense-selected candidate identifier shall exist in the active SPLADE store; missing identifiers shall fail the sparse backend explicitly.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-CANDIDATES

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-QUERY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Query-Side Sparse Encoding
STATEMENT: >>>
RetrieverSplade shall encode query pieces using the query-side sparse encoder.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-OPTION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-DOT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Sparse Similarity
STATEMENT: >>>
Sparse document and query representations shall be compared by deterministic sparse dot product.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-OPTION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-PNORM
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Sparse Piece Aggregation
STATEMENT: >>>
Per-chunk sparse similarities across query pieces shall be clipped at zero and aggregated by p-norm mean.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-OPTION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-P
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Sparse p Value
STATEMENT: >>>
The current sparse p-norm aggregation baseline shall use p = 10 until replaced by approved configuration.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-PNORM

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-SORT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Sparse Deterministic Sort
STATEMENT: >>>
Sparse rows shall be sorted by descending aggregated score and ascending chunk identifier for ties.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-OPTION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-MISSING-STORE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Missing Sparse Store Fallback
STATEMENT: >>>
When the top-level Retriever encounters FileNotFoundError for an older project without a SPLADE store, it shall continue with an empty sparse row list rather than aborting dense retrieval.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-OPTION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-BYPASS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: SPLADE Bypass Contract
STATEMENT: >>>
When SPLADE is disabled, Retriever shall duplicate the dense ranked rows into the second fusion input so the downstream fusion/write-back contract remains unchanged.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-OPTION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-BYPASS-DIAG
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: SPLADE Bypass Observability
STATEMENT: >>>
The system shall expose whether SPLADE used real sparse scores, was unavailable, or was bypassed with dense duplication.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-OPTION

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 7. First Weighted Reciprocal Rank Fusion

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Dense and sparse-ranked rows are fused by one neutral deterministic helper.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-RRF1
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Retrieval RRF Fusion
STATEMENT: >>>
Retriever shall fuse dense and sparse/bypass ranked lists using weighted reciprocal-rank fusion.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-RRF-K
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: RRF Constant
STATEMENT: >>>
The RRF helper shall use a positive configurable rank constant; the current baseline shall be 60.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-RRF1

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-RRF-WEIGHTS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Retrieval Fusion Weights
STATEMENT: >>>
The current retrieval fusion baseline shall weight the dense list 0.75 and the sparse/bypass list 0.25 until replaced by approved JSON configuration.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-RRF1

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-RRF-SCORE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: RRF Score Calculation
STATEMENT: >>>
Each available rank contribution shall equal its branch weight divided by RRF constant plus one-based rank; contributions shall be summed by chunk identifier.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-RRF1

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-RRF-UNION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: RRF Identifier Union
STATEMENT: >>>
The neutral RRF helper shall support the union of identifiers appearing in either input list.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-RRF1

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-RRF-META
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: RRF Metadata
STATEMENT: >>>
The neutral RRF result shall preserve merged metadata and attach generic branch scores, branch ranks, and fused rrf_score when available.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-RRF1

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-RRF-META-MERGE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Conservative Metadata Merge
STATEMENT: >>>
Metadata fusion shall retain an existing key value and shall add only keys absent from the accumulated metadata.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-RRF1

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-RRF-SORT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Fused Deterministic Sort
STATEMENT: >>>
Fused rows shall be ordered by descending fused score and ascending chunk identifier for ties.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-RRF1

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-RRF-CUTOFF
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Fused Retrieval Cutoff
STATEMENT: >>>
The retrieval RRF output shall be limited to the requested positive top_k.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-RRF1

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-RRF-PROJECTION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Retrieval Metadata Projection
STATEMENT: >>>
Retriever shall map neutral RRF branch fields to retrieval-specific emb_score, splade_score, emb_rank, splade_rank, and rrf_score aliases without discarding neutral metadata.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-RRF1

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 8. Source Hydration and Chunk Reconstruction

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Vector stores hold vectors and metadata; raw chunk text is reconstructed from doc_raw.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-HYDRATE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Hydration Requirement
STATEMENT: >>>
Retriever shall hydrate each fused ranked row into a Chunk object before writing request-time document context into SuperPrompt.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-HYDRATE-PATH
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Hydration Source Path
STATEMENT: >>>
Hydration shall resolve metadata path relative to the configured document root.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-HYDRATE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-HYDRATE-INDEX
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Hydration Chunk Index
STATEMENT: >>>
Hydration shall require chunk_idx metadata and shall select the corresponding reconstructed chunk.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-HYDRATE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-HYDRATE-SAME-CONFIG
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Hydration Chunking Consistency
STATEMENT: >>>
Hydration shall use the same effective chunk size and overlap as ingestion for the source-version being reconstructed.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-HYDRATE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-HYDRATE-CACHE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Per-Run Hydration Cache
STATEMENT: >>>
Hydration shall cache source text and reconstructed chunk lists per source path within one retrieval run to avoid repeated reads and splits.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-HYDRATE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-HYDRATE-SKIP-PATH
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Broken Path Skip
STATEMENT: >>>
A ranked row with missing path metadata or a missing raw source file shall be skipped rather than crashing hydration of all other rows.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-HYDRATE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-HYDRATE-SKIP-IDX
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Broken Index Skip
STATEMENT: >>>
A ranked row with absent, negative, or out-of-range chunk index shall be skipped rather than becoming a fabricated chunk.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-HYDRATE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-HYDRATE-ALIGN
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Hydrated Row Alignment
STATEMENT: >>>
The list of valid ranked rows and hydrated Chunk objects shall remain one-to-one and order-aligned.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-HYDRATE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-CHUNK-CONTRACT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Chunk Runtime Contract
STATEMENT: >>>
A hydrated Chunk shall contain stable identifier, project-relative source, snippet, reconstructed source span, and copied metadata.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-HYDRATE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-HYDRATE-NO-MUTATE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Hydration Source Integrity
STATEMENT: >>>
Hydration shall read source files and shall not modify the raw project document or persistent vector metadata.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-HYDRATE

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 9. Retrieval-Stage SuperPrompt Write-Back

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The retrieval stage establishes both a retrieval view and an explicit A3-ready passthrough view.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-WRITE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Retrieval Write-Back
STATEMENT: >>>
Retriever shall write valid hydrated chunks and ordered ranking state into the same SuperPrompt.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-BASE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Base Context Chunks
STATEMENT: >>>
sp.base_context_chunks shall contain hydrated chunks in fused retrieval order.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-WRITE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-VIEW
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Retrieval View
STATEMENT: >>>
sp.views_by_stage["retrieval"] shall contain ordered triples of chunk identifier, retrieval fused score, and SELECTED status.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-WRITE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-PASSTHROUGH
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: A3-Ready Passthrough View
STATEMENT: >>>
Retrieval shall initialize sp.views_by_stage["reranked"] as a copy of retrieval ordering and scores so A3 can run when real ColBERT reranking is not executed.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-WRITE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-PASSTHROUGH-NOT-RERANK
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Passthrough Truthfulness
STATEMENT: >>>
The retrieval-created reranked view shall be marked as passthrough and shall not be represented as a completed ColBERT ranking.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-PASSTHROUGH

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-FINAL-IDS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Retrieval Final IDs
STATEMENT: >>>
sp.final_selection_ids shall equal the ordered identifiers of the valid hydrated retrieval rows.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-WRITE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-STAGE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Retrieval Lifecycle
STATEMENT: >>>
After successful retrieval write-back, sp.stage shall equal retrieval and history_of_stages shall receive retrieval.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-WRITE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-DIAG
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Retrieval Passthrough Diagnostics
STATEMENT: >>>
SuperPrompt extras shall record the A3-ready source, candidate count, and reranked passthrough state.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-WRITE

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 10. Optional ColBERT Reranking Input and Cleaning

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Reranker consumes retrieval candidates and may bypass or execute a ColBERT scoring path.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-ROOT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Reranker Capability
STATEMENT: >>>
Reranker shall optionally rescore and reorder the bounded document candidates already stored by Retrieval.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-PRECONDITION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Reranker Preconditions
STATEMENT: >>>
Reranker shall require a non-empty retrieval view and non-empty base_context_chunks.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-QUERY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Reranker Query Projection
STATEMENT: >>>
Real reranking shall rebuild the current query text through SuperPromptProjector and split it with the configured query-window contract.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-CANDIDATE-CAP
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Reranker Candidate Cap
STATEMENT: >>>
Real or bypass reranking shall process no more than the effective reranker top_k candidates; the current constructor baseline shall be 50.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-MODEL
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current ColBERT Model
STATEMENT: >>>
The current reranker model baseline shall be lightonai/GTE-ModernColBERT-v1 until changed by approved configuration.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-DEVICE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Reranker Device Governance
STATEMENT: >>>
The reranker runtime device shall be configurable and shall be honored by model initialization.

The current constructor default of cpu shall not be claimed as enforced when the backend model is created without applying the device argument.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-CLEAN-DYNAMIC
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Dynamic Cleaning Only
STATEMENT: >>>
Reranker shall clean a temporary scoring copy of each chunk text and shall not alter the stored or hydrated canonical snippet.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-CLEAN-FRONT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Front-Matter Cleaning
STATEMENT: >>>
Reranker cleaning shall remove an initial delimited front-matter block when present.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-CLEAN-DYNAMIC

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-CLEAN-META
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Metadata-Line Cleaning
STATEMENT: >>>
Reranker cleaning shall remove configured line-level metadata keys such as title, author, version, updated, tags, dates, and description.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-CLEAN-DYNAMIC

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-CLEAN-ARTIFACT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Prompt-Artifact Cleaning
STATEMENT: >>>
Reranker cleaning shall remove code-fence marker lines, @@meta lines, and recognized END_OF_PROMPT marker lines while preserving normal content.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-CLEAN-DYNAMIC

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-CLEAN-EMPTY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Empty Cleaned Candidate
STATEMENT: >>>
A candidate whose cleaned scoring text is empty shall be excluded from ColBERT scoring.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-CLEAN-DYNAMIC

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-NO-VALID
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: No Valid Rerank Candidates
STATEMENT: >>>
Real reranking shall fail explicitly when no candidate can be prepared for ColBERT scoring.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-ROOT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 11. ColBERT Scoring and Second Fusion

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
ColBERT scores the same bounded candidate documents for every query piece and the result is fused with retrieval order.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-ENCODE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: ColBERT Encoding
STATEMENT: >>>
Real reranking shall encode query pieces as queries and the cleaned candidate snippets as documents using the configured ColBERT model.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-DOCS-PER-QUERY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Candidate Set per Query Piece
STATEMENT: >>>
Every query piece shall be scored against the same ordered valid candidate identifier and document list.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-ENCODE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-MEAN
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: ColBERT Piece Aggregation
STATEMENT: >>>
For each chunk identifier, ColBERT scores returned across query pieces shall be aggregated by arithmetic mean.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-ENCODE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-COLBERT-SORT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: ColBERT Deterministic Sort
STATEMENT: >>>
Aggregated ColBERT rows shall be ordered by descending mean score and ascending chunk identifier for ties.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-ENCODE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-RRF2
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Second Weighted RRF
STATEMENT: >>>
Reranker shall fuse the original retrieval ranking with the ColBERT ranking through the same neutral weighted RRF helper.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-WEIGHTS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current Reranker Fusion Weights
STATEMENT: >>>
The current second-fusion baseline shall weight Retrieval 0.75 and ColBERT 0.25.

Comments describing equal weighting shall not override the executed values.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-RRF2

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-META-PRESERVE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Retrieval Metadata Preservation
STATEMENT: >>>
Before the second fusion overwrites generic rrf_score, the original retrieval fused score shall be preserved under retrieval_rrf_score when available.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-RRF2

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-META-PROJECT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Reranker Metadata Projection
STATEMENT: >>>
Reranker shall project neutral second-fusion fields to retrieval_score, colbert_score, retrieval_rank, colbert_rank, and rerank_rrf_score.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-RRF2

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-WRITE-META
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Chunk Metadata Write-Back
STATEMENT: >>>
Reranker-specific scores and ranks shall be merged into the hydrated chunk metadata for later diagnostic rendering.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-RRF2

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-FINAL-SORT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Final Rerank Order
STATEMENT: >>>
The final reranked rows shall be sorted by descending rerank fused score and ascending chunk identifier for ties.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-RRF2

[[/SECTION]]

