[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 14. Traceability and Acceptance Criteria

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
These criteria verify the complete retrieval/reranking contract before A3.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-CODE-OWNERSHIP
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Retrieval Code Ownership
STATEMENT: >>>
Retriever, RetrieverEmb, RetrieverSplade, rrf_merge, smart_query_splitter, Chunk, DocScore compatibility, and Reranker shall map to the deepest applicable UIDs in this document.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SIBLING
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Sibling Ownership Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
Document ingestion shall remain owned by 41 and A3/A4 behavior shall remain owned by 43.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-ROOT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-AC-DENSE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Dense Ranking
STATEMENT: >>>
Given a valid project store and query pieces, dense retrieval shall return at most top_k rows ordered by p-norm aggregated cosine score with deterministic tie resolution.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-DENSE-FIRST

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-AC-FLOOR
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Hard Floor
STATEMENT: >>>
Given a positive hard embedding floor, every dense row entering SPLADE/fusion shall have dense score greater than or equal to that floor.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-EMB-FLOOR

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-AC-SPARSE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Dense-Bounded SPLADE
STATEMENT: >>>
Given SPLADE enabled, every sparse-scored identifier shall belong to the dense survivor set and every dense survivor shall be present in the sparse store or the branch shall fail explicitly.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-CANDIDATES

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-AC-SPARSE-BYPASS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: SPLADE Bypass
STATEMENT: >>>
Given SPLADE disabled, retrieval shall complete using dense duplication as the second fusion input and shall expose bypass status.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-SPARSE-BYPASS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-AC-RRF1
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: First Fusion
STATEMENT: >>>
Given two ranked inputs and configured weights, fused scores and order shall match deterministic weighted RRF with the configured rank constant.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-RRF1

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-AC-HYDRATE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Hydration
STATEMENT: >>>
Every row written to the retrieval view shall have a corresponding hydrated Chunk; broken rows shall be omitted from both aligned outputs.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-HYDRATE-ALIGN

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-AC-PASSTHROUGH
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Retrieval Passthrough
STATEMENT: >>>
After retrieval without real reranking, the reranked view shall equal the retrieval view and diagnostics shall identify retrieval_passthrough.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-PASSTHROUGH

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-AC-COLBERT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: ColBERT Reranking
STATEMENT: >>>
Given real reranking enabled and valid candidates, ColBERT mean scores shall be fused with retrieval ranking using the configured second-fusion values and shall produce the reranked view.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-RRF2

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-AC-RERANK-BYPASS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: ColBERT Bypass
STATEMENT: >>>
Given ColBERT disabled, no ColBERT model call shall occur and retrieval order shall be copied into the reranked stage.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-BYPASS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-AC-CLEAN
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Non-Mutating Cleaning
STATEMENT: >>>
Reranker cleaning shall alter only the temporary scoring text; the corresponding base_context_chunks snippets shall remain unchanged.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-CLEAN-DYNAMIC

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-AC-WEIGHTS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Executed Weight Truth
STATEMENT: >>>
The effective retrieval and reranking weights reported for the current baseline shall be 0.75/0.25 unless validated JSON configuration overrides them in implemented code.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RERANK-WEIGHTS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-AC-CONFIG
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: JSON Parameter Migration
STATEMENT: >>>
After configuration migration, changing a retrieval limit, p value, RRF constant, branch weight, model, device, or query window shall require only validated JSON change and shall be reflected in diagnostics.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-CONFIG-JSON

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-AC-SYNC
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AC: Requirement-Code Synchronization
STATEMENT: >>>
A retrieval baseline shall not be accepted when query routing, branch scope, fusion weights, hydration semantics, passthrough meaning, or reranking write-back contradicts this document.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-DOC-RETRIEVE-CODE-OWNERSHIP

[[/SECTION]]
